    "body": "I was looking yet again at the parser for cython and I figured something like the print or exec statement handlings could also be used to add an inline_ statement - the purpose which would dump strings directly into the emitted code.  The idea is to use it globally and within functions.\r\n\r\nIs the naming good?\r\n\r\nAny ideas what this would break / be weary of?\r\n\r\nSuch a statement could be used to do macros, pull in includes, and modify/declare c-variables.",
